<!--
  Czech (cs) localization.

  Translation philosophy:
  - Natural, idiomatic Czech — NOT literal 1:1 from English.
  - Formal register ("vy" form) throughout.
  - Match affordance: buttons = infinitive verb ("Uložit"), headers = noun phrase,
    dialogs with a question = question form, microcopy = full sentence with period.
  - Use the Czech speciality-coffee community's actual vocabulary, not dictionary
    calques. See .github/instructions/translations.instructions.md for the canonical
    glossary and conventions.

  Key loanwords (kept in English because Czech baristas actually use them):
    bloom        — not "předsmáčení" (too clinical; roasters write "bloom")
    decaf        — acceptable alongside "bezkofeinová" in consumer copy
    drawdown, preinfusion, bypass — technical loanwords

  Bag terminology unified on "balení" (neuter) — consistent across the app.
  Agreeing adjectives are neuter: Zapečetěné, Otevřené, etc.
-->
